main event: Multiple military personnel observed a fast-moving unidentified object over Camp Irwin, California on September 26, 1960.
interesting points: The object was described as a sphere, as large as a tractor, trailing flames and smoke.
The object was brighter than the sky, with a brightness comparable to a headlight.
The object moved at an estimated speed of 3,000 feet per minute, or 400-450 mph, in a straight and steady course parallel to the hills.
The sighting lasted for about 30 seconds before the object went out of sight.
The observers included six persons pulling a trailer, but their identities were not provided.
